`Could we not still send messages to him and obtain his help?'
`But within those bounds nothing seems to dismay him,'
'Then,'
`It seems that he has a power even over the Ring.'
`Would he not take the Ring and keep it there, for ever harmless?'
`there are but two courses, as Glorfindel already has declared: to hide the Ring for ever; or to unmake it. But both are beyond our power. Who will read this riddle for us?'
`and yet we come no nearer. What strength have we for the finding of the Fire in which it was made? That is the path of despair. Of folly I would say, if the long wisdom of Elrond did not forbid me.'
